{
  "text": "Such trophic effects of ACTH were reported in human adrenal gland cells and skin melanocytes [CITATION_1] . Several studies documented what was referred to as 'ectopic ACTH syndrome' whereby several cancers from endocrine sites such as the pituitary gland [CITATION_2] and diverse non-endocrine sites including the prostate gland, lung, liver, pancreas, and neuronal tissue, secrete ACTH that drives cell proliferation in these tissues [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
